<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 5:57PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL DEFIANCE AND NORTH
CENTRAL PAULDING COUNTIES THROUGH 630 PM EDT...
At 557 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Paulding, or 9 miles east of Hicksville, moving
southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
